@section atom_type_sec atom_type

@addindex atom_type

@b Syntax:

@verbatim
atom_type	name attributes
@endverbatim

@li @a name = name of the atom type being defined @n
@li @a attributes = space-separated list of attributes related to the defined atom type

@b Examples:

@verbatim
atom_type	CH3 0.1947 3.75
atom_type	CH2 0.0914 3.95
@endverbatim

@b Description:

This command defines an atom type with its related attributes.

The parameter @a name is a single character string without spaces and without wildcard characters * and ?.

@sa @ref atom_sec

<hr>

@section bond_type_sec bond_type

@addindex bond_type

@b Syntax:

@verbatim
bond_type	atom-type-1 atom-type-2 attributes
@endverbatim

@li @a atom-type-x = name of a previously defined atom type @n
@li @a attributes = space-separated list of attributes related to the defined bond type

@b Examples:

@verbatim
bond_type	CH3 CH2 95.877 1.54
bond_type	CH2 CH? 95.877 1.54
bond_type	C* C* 95.877 1.54
@endverbatim

@b Description:

This command defines a bond type with its related attributes. The bond type is identified by the
types of the atoms involved, which must have been previously defined.

The parameters @a atom-type-1 and @a atom-type-2 are names of atom types that have already been
defined. In both @a atom-type-1 and @a atom-type-2, one can use wildcard characters to make
simultaneous reference to more than one atom type.

@sa @ref atom_type_sec, @ref bond_sec

